The paper discusses the integration of LTE and Wi-Fi networks at the radio access network level, which falls under the category of network integration and communication protocols. Therefore, cs.NI (Networked Systems) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the performance evaluation of the proposed architecture, which involves the use of information theory and communication theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a likely sub-category as well. The paper also mentions simulations and evaluations, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses potential challenges and security issues, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
